5	4	TP DJANGO N1 EN	Practice building a django app 	Django	t	C:\\xampp\\htdocs\\Public_library_codebase\\storage\\uploads\\documents\\4\\8058bc64a48162ed40e386ad33dcbee0.pdf	\N	2026-04-14 18:21:47.740282	Practical Work – Development of a Neighborhood\r\nManagement Application with Django\r\n1. Lab Statement\r\nAs part of this practical work, you are invited to design and develop a\r\nweb application for neighborhood management using the Django framework.\r\nThis application will allow managers to handle neighborhoods, house\r\ncategories, and houses through a secure interface.\r\n2. Context\r\nThe municipality wishes to digitize the management of its residential\r\nareas. To this end, an application is planned to allow managers to create and\r\nmonitor the development of the neighborhoods they are responsible for, as well\r\nas the houses built within them. Each house belongs to a specific category (e.g.,\r\nvilla, studio, apartment building, etc.) and cannot exist independently of a\r\nneighborhood. Everything must be administered via an intuitive, secure, and\r\nwell-structured interface.\r\n3. Educational Objectives\r\nAt the end of this lab, the student should be able to:\r\n★​Create a complete Django application with several related models.\r\n★​Use the Django administration interface to manage certain objects.\r\n★​Set up a secure user interface with authentication.\r\n★​Implement basic CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations for\r\nmultiple entities.\r\n★​Apply business constraints at the model level.\r\n★​Restrict data access according to the logged-in user.\r\n\r\n\f4. Expected Features\r\nThe application must provide the following features:\r\nA. Authentication\r\n★​A manager can log in to the user interface.\r\n★​Managers are added exclusively via the Django admin interface.\r\nB. Neighborhood Management\r\n★​A manager can create, list, modify, and delete the neighborhoods\r\nthey manage.\r\n★​Each neighborhood has a name, a description, and an area (in m²).\r\n★​A manager can only see and manage the neighborhoods they have\r\ncreated.\r\nC. House Management\r\n★​Each house must belong to an existing neighborhood.\r\n★​A house has an address, an area, a category, and is linked to a\r\nneighborhood.\r\n★​A manager can create several houses in a neighborhood, provided\r\nthat the total area of the houses is strictly less than that of the\r\nneighborhood.\r\n★​Full CRUD operations on houses.\r\nD. House Category Management\r\n★​A category corresponds to a type of house (e.g., villa, studio, etc.).\r\n★​Each house belongs to only one category.\r\n★​A neighborhood can include several categories of houses.\r\n★​Full CRUD operations on categories.\r\nE. Entity Details\r\n★​Detailed display of a neighborhood's information along with the list\r\nof its houses.\r\n★​Display of a house's details (neighborhood, category, area, etc.).\r\n\r\n\f5. Constraints\r\n★​A neighborhood cannot contain more houses than its area allows.\r\n★​A house can only be created if a neighborhood already exists.\r\n★​Data operations are restricted to the logged-in manager.\r\n★​The Django admin interface must only be used for creating managers.\r\n★​The application must use the standard Django authentication system.\r\n6. Remarks\r\n★​The user interface can remain simple (basic HTML/CSS or with\r\nBootstrap).\r\n★​Remember to protect views with decorators like login_required.\r\n★​The permission system can be handled with a simple check to ensure the\r\nuser owns the objects.\r\n★​Use Django relationships (ForeignKey, OneToMany, etc.) to model the\r\nentities.\r\n★​Area constraint validation must be implemented in the model or the house\r\ncreation form.\r\n\r\nDue Date: Wednesday, April 13, 2026 !\r\n“School is not a trap; together let's fight against last-minute work.”\r\n\r\n\fGrading Rubric\r\nCriteria\r\n\r\nExpected Detail\r\n\r\nPoints\r\n\r\n1. Correct entity\r\nmodeling\r\n\r\nManager, Neighborhood, House, Category models well-defined with\r\ncorrect relationships (ForeignKey, OneToMany, etc.)\r\n\r\n4 pts\r\n\r\n2. Implementation of\r\nCRUD features\r\n\r\nImplementation of basic operations for the 4 entities (create, update,\r\ndelete, read)\r\n\r\n4 pts\r\n\r\n3. Django\r\nadministration\r\ninterface\r\n\r\nPresence of entities in Django Admin + creation of managers via\r\nadmin\r\n\r\n2 pts\r\n\r\n4. Authentication and\r\npermissions\r\n\r\nLogin required to access views / only the logged-in manager's data is\r\naccessible\r\n\r\n3 pts\r\n\r\n5. Business constraints\r\nrespected\r\n\r\nVerification that the sum of house areas < neighborhood area, house\r\ncreation prohibited without a neighborhood, etc.\r\n\r\n3 pts\r\n\r\n6. View details\r\n\r\nDetailed display of a neighborhood and a house (with associated data)\r\n\r\n2 pts\r\n\r\n7. Code quality and\r\nproject organization\r\n\r\nClear structure, adherence to Django conventions, well-organized\r\nfiles\r\n\r\n2 pts\r\n\r\nTotal :\r\n\r\n/ 20\r\n\r\n\f	'1':11,529 '13':507 '2':53,549,583,642,660 '20':663 '2026':508 '3':130,568,604,626 '4':199,547,560,566,585 '5':387,606 '6':440,628 '7':644 'abl':143 'access':191,592,603 'accord':192 'add':222 'address':283 'adher':652 'admin':227,422,577,582 'administ':120 'administr':157,570 'allow':40,74,398 'along':370 'alreadi':408 'apart':107 'appli':182 'applic':8,29,38,70,149,203,432 'april':506 'area':65,253,285,307,385,397,489,616,618 'associ':640 'authent':170,210,438,586 'b':229 'basic':172,448,556 'belong':99,274,342 'bootstrap':452 'build':108 'built':94 'busi':183,607 'c':268 'cannot':111,391 'categori':46,103,287,326,329,346,352,359,384,536 'certain':161 'check':471 'clear':650 'code':645 'complet':147 'constraint':184,388,490,608 'contain':392 'context':54 'convent':655 'correct':530,542 'correspond':330 'creat':77,145,174,235,267,297,404,429,562 'creation':501,578,620 'criteria':525 'crud':173,320,356,552 'd':324 'data':190,410,601,641 'date':504 'decor':458 'defin':540 'delet':177,239,56