10	4	Cost Accounting Concepts.pdf	Study Cost accounting concepts	Accounting	t	C:\\xampp\\htdocs\\Public_library_codebase\\storage\\uploads\\documents\\4\\122fe4fd80207c305158331dd2c0279f.pdf	\N	2026-04-22 11:08:23.178267	Cost Accounting Concepts\r\nCost Accounting: A method of collecting, recording, and analysing the cost incurred in carrying out\r\nan activity.\r\n\r\nImportance of Cost Accounting\r\na. To management\r\n- Ascertainment of cost using techniques such as Job Costing and Process Costing\r\n- Aids in price fixation\r\n- Cost reduction on the long run\r\n- Elimination of wastage\r\n- Helps check accuracy of financial account\r\nb. To Employees: Provides data for incentive plans, which can increase productivity\r\nc. To Creditors: Suppliers and investors use these reports to judge the profitability and earning\r\ncapacity.\r\nd. To National Economy: Better cost accounting leads to better productivity, hence increase in\r\ngovernment revenue\r\n\r\nDefinition and Classifications of Cost\r\nCost: Estimate of the amount of money needed to produce a product or perform a service.\r\n\r\nBreakdown of Costs\r\n\r\nProduct Cost: Cost associated to manufacturing (e.g., direct materials, direct labour, factory costs\r\nlike electricity, rent)\r\nPeriod Cost: Cost not tied to the production process (e.g., marketing, executives’ salaries)\r\nDirect Materials Cost: Cost of materials (e.g an OLED screen for a phone)\r\n\r\n\fDirect Labour cost: Cost of wages of those involved in the production (E.g assembly line worker in\r\nfactory)\r\nOverhead Cost: Cost that cannot easily be measured per unit produced (e.g Cost of machinery,\r\nelectricity)\r\nFixed Cost: Does not vary with production volume (e.g The monthly rent for a factory building.You\r\npay the same rent no matter the amount of goods produced)\r\nVariable Cost: Varies with production volume (e.g Shipping boxes used for phones. The mpre you sell\r\nphones, the more you buy boxes)\r\nSunk cost: Cost that can’t be recovered or changed by future decisions (e.g spending 1 milion on\r\nresearch and development cannot be recovered)\r\nOpportunity Cost: The profit lost by making a decision. E.g, If the company uses the factory to make\r\nphones, it can’t be used to make tablets. The profit lost in not making tablets is the opportunity cost\r\nof making phones.\r\n\r\n\f	'1':267 'account':2,5,24,58,93,318,320 'accuraci':55 'activ':20 'aid':40 'amount':112,226 'analys':12 'ascertain':28 'assembl':182 'associ':130 'b':59 'better':91,96 'box':238,251 'breakdown':124 'building.you':218 'buy':250 'c':71 'cannot':191,273 'capac':86 'carri':17 'chang':261 'check':54 'classif':105 'collect':9 'compani':288 'concept':3 'concepts.pdf':319 'cost':1,4,14,23,30,36,39,44,92,107,108,126,128,129,139,144,145,158,159,171,172,188,189,199,204,231,253,254,277,313,317 'creditor':73 'd':87 'data':63 'decis':264,284 'definit':103 'develop':272 'direct':134,136,156,169 'e.g':133,152,162,181,198,211,236,265,285 'earn':85 'easili':192 'economi':90 'electr':141,202 'elimin':50 'employe':61 'estim':109 'execut':154 'factori':138,186,217,291 'financi':57 'fix':203 'fixat':43 'futur':263 'good':228 'govern':101 'help':53 'henc':98 'import':21 'incent':65 'increas':69,99 'incur':15 'investor':76 'involv':177 'job':35 'judg':81 'labour':137,170 'lead':94 'like':140 'line':183 'long':48 'lost':280,305 'machineri':201 'make':282,293,301,308,315 'manag':27 'manufactur':132 'market':153 'materi':135,157,161 'matter':224 'measur':194 'method':7 'milion':268 'money':114 'month':213 'mpre':243 'nation':89 'need':115 'ole':164 'opportun':276,312 'overhead':187 'pay':219 'per':195 'perform':121 'period':143 'phone':168,241,246,294,316 'plan':66 'price':42 'process':38,151 'produc':117,197,229 'product':70,97,119,127,150,180,209,234 'profit':83,279,304 'provid':62 'record':10 'recov':259,275 'reduct':45 'rent':142,214,222 'report':79 'research':270 'revenu':102 'run':49 'salari':155 'screen':165 'sell':245 'servic':123 's