15	3	Specification_Angular_Django1		Angular Project	t	C:\\xampp\\htdocs\\Public_library_codebase\\storage\\uploads\\documents\\3\\bd8d93abe358d202902eb58398f8281a.pdf	\N	2026-04-29 07:58:58.344428	SPECIFICATION\r\nDOCUMENT\r\nBus Reservation Platform\r\n\r\n2026\r\n\r\nKenvo Fomazou Samuel\r\nsamuel.kenvo@saintjeaningenieur.org\r\n\r\n\fContents\r\n1.\r\n\r\nIntroduction ............................................................................................................................. 2\r\n\r\n2.\r\n\r\nDescription .............................................................................................................................. 3\r\n\r\n3. Objectives................................................................................................................................... 4\r\n3.1 General Objective ............................................................................................................... 4\r\n3.2 Specific Objectives .............................................................................................................. 4\r\n1. Facilitate Advance Intercity Booking .............................................................................. 4\r\n2. Improve Schedule Transparency ..................................................................................... 4\r\n3. Prevent Overbooking and Seat Conflicts ....................................................................... 4\r\n4. Strengthen Revenue and Fleet Control .......................................................................... 4\r\n5. Enhance Security and Ticket Authenticity ...................................................................... 4\r\n6. Improve Passenger Experience ........................................................................................ 4\r\n4.\r\n\r\nMain Functionalities................................................................................................................ 5\r\n4.1 Passenger Account Management .................................................................................... 5\r\n4.2 Intercity Route Management ............................................................................................. 5\r\n4.3 Bus and Fleet Configuration ............................................................................................... 5\r\n4.4 Real-Time Seat Reservation System ................................................................................... 5\r\n4.5 Booking and Confirmation Workflow ................................................................................ 6\r\n4.6 Payment Integration ............................................................................................................ 6\r\n4.7 Electronic Ticketing System ................................................................................................. 6\r\n4.8 Terminal Validation Module................................................................................................ 7\r\n4.9 Operator Dashboard ........................................................................................................... 7\r\n4.10 Administrator Control System ........................................................................................... 7\r\n4.11 Reporting and Analytics.................................................................................................... 7\r\n4.12 Notification System ............................................................................................................ 7\r\n\r\n5.\r\n\r\nConclusion............................................................................................................................... 9\r\n\r\n1\r\nsamuel.kenvo@saintjeaningenieur.org\r\n\r\nSaint Jean Ingénieur\r\n\r\n\f1. Introduction\r\nIn a fast-paced environment like ours, mastery of recent technologies is of utmost\r\nimportance as aspiring software developers. As a student of Saint Jean Ingénieur,\r\nI have decided to address real life problems through working solutions. This work\r\nis a final project of our course Angular and Django.\r\nThis document presents the technical and functional specification of a Bus\r\nReservation Platform developed using Angular as the frontend framework and\r\nDjango as the backend framework. The system is designed to digitize bus ticket\r\nbooking operations, streamline transport company management, and improve\r\npassenger experience through online reservations, secure payments, and real-time\r\nseat tracking.\r\nThe platform aims to eliminate inefficiencies associated with manual ticketing\r\nsystems such as overbooking, poor record management, long queues, lack of\r\ntransparency, and limited accessibility. It provides a centralized system where\r\npassengers can search routes, compare schedules, select seats, make payments,\r\nand receive digital tickets. Transport companies can manage buses, routes,\r\npricing, schedules, reports, and user data through an administrative dashboard.\r\nThe architecture follows a modern client-server design with RESTful APIs,\r\nsecure authentication mechanisms, and scalable infrastructure. This document\r\ndefines the system’s purpose, operational context, functional scope, and\r\nperformance expectations\r\n\r\n2\r\nsamuel.kenvo@saintjeaningenieur.org\r\n\r\nSaint Jean Ingénieur\r\n\r\n\f2. Description\r\nThe Bus Reservation Platform is a web-based intercity travel management system designed to\r\nfacilitate the booking and administration of long-distance bus journeys between cities.\r\nBuilt using Angular (frontend) and Django (backend), the system provides a centralized\r\ndigital infrastructure connecting passengers, intercity bus operators, and system administrators.\r\nThe platform focuses specifically on:\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nLong-distance routes (City A → City B)\r\nScheduled departures\r\nReserved seating\r\nPrepaid ticketing\r\nStructured fleet management\r\n\r\nUnlike informal or intra-city transport systems, intercity travel requires:\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nAdvance booking\r\nStructured scheduling\r\nFixed departure times\r\nSeat assignment\r\nIdentity-based ticketing\r\nOrganized passenger manifests\r\n\r\nThe system supports multiple intercity transport companies operating across different routes.\r\nIt provides real-time seat availability, automated booking confirmation, digital ticket issuance,\r\nand financial tracking tools.\r\nTechnically, the architecture includes:\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nRole-based access control\r\nSecure payment integration\r\nQR-based ticket validation\r\nScalable database infrastructure\r\n\r\nThe platform ensures reliability, security, and operational transparency for structured intercity\r\ntransportation networks.\r\n\r\n3\r\nsamuel.kenvo@saintjeaningenieur.org\r\n\r\nSaint Jean Ingénieur\r\n\r\n\f3. Objectives\r\n3.1 General Objective\r\nTo design a secure, efficient, and scalable digital platform that modernizes intercity bus\r\nticketing and fleet management operations.\r\n\r\n3.2 Specific Objectives\r\n1. Facilitate Advance Intercity Booking\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nAllow passengers to reserve seats before travel date\r\nReduce terminal congestion\r\nEnsure confirmed seat allocation\r\nProvide guaranteed travel planning\r\n\r\n2. Improve Schedule Transparency\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nDisplay available intercity routes\r\nShow fixed departure and arrival times\r\nProvide estimated travel duration\r\nOffer fare comparison options\r\n\r\n3. Prevent Overbooking and Seat Conflicts\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nReal-time seat tracking\r\nAutomated seat locking during checkout\r\nCentralized booking database\r\n\r\n4. Strengthen Revenue and Fleet Control\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nRoute-based revenue analytics\r\nBus occupancy rate tracking\r\nTrip performance monitoring\r\nOperator dashboard controls\r\n\r\n5. Enhance Security and Ticket Authenticity\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nQR-code-based ticket validation\r\nDigital passenger manifests\r\nIdentity-linked bookings\r\nFraud prevention mechanisms\r\n\r\n6. Improve Passenger Experience\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nOnline payment options\r\nInstant ticket delivery\r\nBooking history tracking\r\nCancellation and rescheduling features\r\n4\r\n\r\nsamuel.kenvo@saintjeaningenieur.org\r\n\r\nSaint Jean Ingénieur\r\n\r\n\f4. Main Functionalities\r\nThe system is structured around modules specifically tailored to intercity operations.\r\n\r\n4.1 Passenger Account Management\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nUser registration and login\r\nProfile management\r\nTravel history tracking\r\n\r\nPassengers must provide identification details required for intercity travel compliance.\r\n\r\n4.2 Intercity Route Management\r\nOperators can:\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nDefine departure city and destination city\r\nSet fixed departure times\r\nSpecify arrival estimates\r\nAssign buses to routes\r\nAdjust seasonal pricing\r\n\r\nPassengers can:\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nSearch by origin city\r\nSelect destination\r\nChoose departure date\r\nFilter by time and price\r\n\r\n4.3 Bus and Fleet Configuration\r\nOperators can:\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nRegister buses\r\nDefine seating capacity\r\nConfigure seating layout (Standard, VIP, Executive)\r\nAssign buses to specific intercity routes\r\n\r\nFleet management includes maintenance tracking capabilities (optional extension).\r\n\r\n4.4 Real-Time Seat Reservation System\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nVisual seat map interface\r\nSeat availability indicators\r\nTemporary seat locking during checkout\r\nAutomatic seat release if payment fails\r\n\r\nThis is critical in intercity travel where seating is guaranteed and pre-assigned.\r\n5\r\nsamuel.kenvo@saintjeaningenieur.org\r\n\r\nSaint Jean Ingénieur\r\n\r\n\f4.5 Booking and Confirmation Workflow\r\nBooking steps:\r\n1.\r\n2.\r\n3.\r\n4.\r\n5.\r\n6.\r\n\r\nRoute selection\r\nDeparture date selection\r\nSeat selection\r\nPassenger detail confirmation\r\nPayment processing\r\nBooking confirmation\r\n\r\nThe system generates:\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nUnique booking reference\r\nDigital travel receipt\r\nPassenger manifest entry\r\n\r\n4.6 Payment Integration\r\nSupports:\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nCard payments\r\nMobile money services\r\nOnline payment gateways\r\n\r\nFeatures include:\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nTransaction validation\r\nPayment logging\r\nRefund and cancellation management\r\n\r\nBooking confirmation depends strictly on successful payment verification.\r\n\r\n4.7 Electronic Ticketing System\r\nAfter payment:\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nAutomatic e-ticket generation\r\nQR code for terminal scanning\r\nPDF ticket download\r\nEmail ticket dispatch\r\n\r\nTicket details include:\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nPassenger name\r\nSeat number\r\nRoute\r\nDeparture time\r\nBus number\r\n6\r\n\r\nsamuel.kenvo@saintjeaningenieur.org\r\n\r\nSaint Jean Ingénieur\r\n\r\n\f•\r\n\r\nOperator information\r\n\r\n4.8 Terminal Validation Module\r\nAt departure terminal:\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nStaff scan QR code\r\nValidate ticket authenticity\r\nConfirm passenger check-in\r\nPrevent duplicate entry\r\n\r\nThis ensures controlled boarding for intercity trips.\r\n\r\n4.9 Operator Dashboard\r\nIntercity operators can:\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nMonitor upcoming departures\r\nView passenger lists\r\nTrack revenue per route\r\nAdjust seat pricing\r\nCancel or reschedule trips\r\nGenerate performance reports\r\n\r\n4.10 Administrator Control System\r\nSystem administrators can:\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nApprove new operators\r\nMonitor global transactions\r\nAccess audit logs\r\nManage dispute resolution\r\nConfigure platform settings\r\n\r\n4.11 Reporting and Analytics\r\nAnalytics include:\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nRoute profitability\r\nBus occupancy percentage\r\nSeasonal demand trends\r\nCity-to-city travel frequency\r\nRevenue growth over time\r\n\r\n4.12 Notification System\r\nAutomatic notifications for:\r\n•\r\n\r\nBooking confirmation\r\n7\r\n\r\nsamuel.kenvo@saintjeaningenieur.org\r\n\r\nSaint Jean Ingénieur\r\n\r\n\f•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nPayment confirmation\r\nDeparture reminders\r\nTrip cancellation alerts\r\nSchedule changes\r\n\r\nDelivery channels:\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nEmail\r\nSMS (optional)\r\nIn-app alerts\r\n\r\n8\r\nsamuel.kenvo@saintjeaningenieur.org\r\n\r\nSaint Jean Ingénieur\r\n\r\n\f5. Conclusion\r\nThe ntercity Bus Reservation Platform is a structured digital ecosystem specifically designed\r\nfor long-distance scheduled transport between cities. By leveraging Angular and Django, the\r\nsystem delivers:\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n•\r\n\r\nSecure advance booking\r\nReal-time seat allocation\r\nStructured departure management\r\nFraud-resistant ticketing\r\nData-driven operator insights\r\n\r\nThe platform enhances efficiency, reduces operational errors, improves passenger experience,\r\nand strengthens financial transparency in the intercity travel sector.\r\n\r\n9\r\nsamuel.kenvo@saintjeaningenieur.org\r\n\r\nSaint Jean Ingénieur\r\n\r\n\f	'1':12,29,135,140,538,830 '2':14,15,35,340,345,562,831 '2026':6 '3':17,18,40,507,512,584,832 '3.1':21,514 '3.2':25,535 '4':20,24,28,34,39,46,47,53,60,65,66,603,663,668,833 '4.1':70,682 '4.10':118,988 '4.11':123,1010 '4.12':128,1034 '4.2':75,705 '4.3':80,747 '4.4':86,779 '4.5':94,823 '4.6':100,862 '4.7':104,892 '4.8':109,933 '4.9':114,962 '5':54,69,74,79,85,93,132,624,818,834,1070 '6':61,99,103,108,646,835,926 '7':113,117,122,127,131,1042 '8':1065 '9':134,1139 'access':271,481,1001 'account':72,684 'across':454 'address':173 'adjust':728,978 'administr':119,306,366,396,989,993 'advanc':31,430,540,1101 'aim':249 'alert':1053,1064 'alloc':557,1107 'allow':543 'analyt':126,613,1013,1014 'angular':189,207,377,1094,1145,1147 'api':319 'app':1063 'approv':995 'architectur':309,476 'around':675 'arriv':574,722 'aspir':159 'assign':438,724,765,817 'associ':253 'audit':1002 'authent':59,321,629,946 'autom':464,595